text: This is perfect. More movies like this from the people said to be "excluded." There is a belief out there that "equal opportunity" will engender 'equal results," so let's put it to the test then, shall we?. They only way American's will understand that talent is real, something you are born with, not something artificially inseminated in a diversity seminar,  is to go along with this liberal, Kabuki theater until American's start accepting, it doesn't matter if a movie is made by 100% white males, or 100% transgender eskimo's, all we care about is whether it is quality or not. You haven't seen nothing yet. Wait until a movie gets made where the writer, the director, the producer,, everyone--are these so called "excluded ones." The studios, who in a sane society would say "no way, I'm investing millions in this," are now just starting to be shamed into believing that their "unconscious bias" is the reason why the terrible, amateurish,schlock they are being pitched, is the next "Silence of the Lambs" or Schindler's List" but they are just too unconsciously bias to see it. "Why some university professor in a mandatory diversity seminar told me so! That's why I thought "Uncle Drew" sounded like utter crap when it came across my desk, and in the name of historical reciprocity, I am going to give them $20 million to make it!" The truth is, nobody every excluded anyone in this country who had real talent. Real talent overcomes all obstacles. That's why we know who Jimi hendrix, Michael Jordan, and  Charlie Parker are.  We should never know who Charles Stone III is, but this is 2018 and this America. More to come.

text: The movie was mixed to me. The basketball scenes were good (I'm a bball fan). The acting and dialogue were not very good overall, making for more cringeworthy comedic scenes than actual funny scenes. All the characters were over-the-top. Kyrie did ok as Drew, his schick was bearable. Reggie Miller and Chris Webber tried their best, Nate's character didnt talk much so he was okay. Lisa Leslie was awful, really couldnt bring over the angry wife character at all. The worse actor was Shaq. He was Terrible. Just too over the top and could not convey the emotions of Big Fella at all. I tried to laugh at him but he was just too weird. Lil Rel did well, as did Nick Kroll. Tiffany Hadish was annoying and a bit too over-the-top. The other lady was just shameless eye candy. The trailer gave away ALL the funny scenes as well. At least the basketball scenes were decent enough

I didn't know that Uncle Drew, Boots, Sights And Preacher were played by real NBA players I knew about Shaq though. And the movie has some good references from other stuff like for example Shaq who plays Big Fella is a karate instructor and his students call him Shaq Fu. And Dax who is played by Lil Rel Howery who was in Get Out tells Uncle Drew that he has seen the movie. The acting, story, directing and comedy is great in this movie and you end up liking these characters, it makes you want to see more. If you have not seen this movie then I recommend you do. This movie is cinematastic rating 5/5
